snippet.textDisplay:
I don't think Lew gonna see this comment, BUT , it would be nice if you stop calling what should be a regular 3.5mm audio jack a "mini jack", 'cause it's not, the 2.5mm jack IS a mini jack (like the one on an old Xbox 360 controller).


PS: Yes I know on Wikipedia it's say the 3.5mm jack is a "miniature size jack", but I never heard anyone call it that way.
To me it always been like this:
2.5mm = mini audio jack
(use in old cell phone, Xbox 360 controller and some weird Chinese electronic)
3.5mm = audio jack
(use in almost all current cell phone (excluding iPhone), all game controller and anything that as audio output)
6.35mm = big audio jack
(use in high-end audio equipment and almost all electric music instrument)
